About Kokālika
At Sāvatthī
Now at that time the Buddha had gone into retreat for the days meditation
Then the independent brahmās Subrahmā and Suddhāvāsa went to the Buddha and stationed themselves one by each doorpost
Then Subrahmā recited this verse about the mendicant Kokālika in the Buddhas presence
What wise person here would judge
the immeasurable by measuring them
I think anyone whod do such a thing
must be an ordinary person wrapped in darkness
