Second The Brahmin Life
At Sāvatthī
Mendicants I will teach you life as a brahmin and the goal of life as a brahmin
And what is life as a brahmin
It is simply this noble eightfold path that is
right view right thought right speech right action right livelihood right effort right mindfulness and right immersion
This is called life as a brahmin
And what is the goal of life as a brahmin
The ending of greed hate and delusion
This is called the goal of life as a brahmin
Linked Discourses
Floods
Tendencies
Mendicants there are these seven underlying tendencies
What seven
The underlying tendencies of sensual desire repulsion views doubt conceit desire to be reborn and ignorance
These are the seven underlying tendencies
The noble eightfold path should be developed for the direct knowledge complete understanding finishing and giving up of these seven underlying tendencies
