Practice
Second Practice
At Sāvatthī
Mendicants I will teach you one practicing wrongly and one practicing rightly
And who is practicing wrongly
Its someone who has wrong view wrong thought wrong speech wrong action wrong livelihood wrong effort wrong mindfulness and wrong immersion
This is called one practicing wrongly
And who is practicing rightly
Its someone who has right view right thought right speech right action right livelihood right effort right mindfulness and right immersion
This is called one practicing rightly
Linked Discourses
Meditation
First Purified
At Sāvatthī
Mendicants these eight things dont arise to be purified bright flawless and rid of corruptions except when a Realized One a perfected one a fully awakened Buddha has appeared
What eight
They are right view right thought right speech right action right livelihood right effort right mindfulness and right immersion
These eight things dont arise to be purified bright flawless and rid of corruptions except when a Realized One a perfected one a fully awakened Buddha has appeared
